). About 1.96× cephalic length. Mean length ratio of antenna segments I: II, III, IV = 1: 1.6, 3.1, 6.8. Ant. I with six normal chaetae on anterior side, and one small microchaeta in apical part on posterior side (
Fig. 1
). Ant. II with eight apical chaetae, three medial and three basal, one basal internal much longer (~3×) than other two (
